nodes.title: Negative Prompt
widgets_values: facial hair, acne, plastic, smooth, glossy, cartoon, anime, worst quality, low quality, illustration, 3d, 2d, painting, cartoons, sketch

Play with the denoise and seed value.

Higher denoise --> more change to the face

New seed --> new random noise (Although it's random, some seeds give better results than others!)

Play with which facial features you want to change.

- features set to "true" will change
- features set to "false" it will be retained)
Bypass (ctrl+B) the "LoraLoaderModelOnly" if you do not want to add freckles (also add/remove "freckles" from the prompt)

nodes.title: Workflow v0.32a
widgets_values:
- Can upscale any image to 8K and beyond
- Takes 2-4 min on RTX 3080 12GB, 10.5GB usage at 1280 input res
- Uses lots of RAM 64GB+, page-file absolutely necessary on low RAM systems
- Caching SeedVR2 model increases generation speed but memory leaks
- You don't NEED to use SDXL, it is more like a restore / denoise option to add / refine details that otherwise aren't there. You can bypass group.
- You can stack as many times as you want, sometimes SDXL first is better you can change the order

Need help? https://discord.gg/hq8qPbvznf

My preferred SDXL model: https://civitai.com/models/133005/juggernaut-xl

ControlNet model: https://huggingface.co/xinsir/controlnet-tile-sdxl-1.0/resolve/main/diffusion_pytorch_model.safetensors

Known Issues
----
- Color shift on SDXL
- Garbage in garbage out

Best Settings
----
fast_mode = true
sampler (i only tested these) = 
          dpmpp_2m_sde (fast_mode off)
          euler_a (fast_mode on)
custom_denoise = 0.1-0.3
prompt = usually blank is best, sometimes "close up" gives good textures
